- First time renting in 2017, everything is new
- Roof deck w views of Brooklyn and parts of Manhattan
- Onsite, secured parking for 1 vehicle

- 50” HDTV w Netflix

- 25min drive to Manhattan
- Fully equipped + stocked kitchen
- Extremely safe neighborhood
- Walk Score 98 (‘Walker’s Paradise’)

The apartment comes with a well-equipped kitchen, high-speed WiFi, cable TV and a 50" HDTV. NETFLIX . 
The apartment is professionally cleaned before each guest's arrival. If you need to do laundry, there is a laundry room on the ground floor that is shared between all the tenants in the building

review.comments: This place is a gem in a not so great neighborhood although it is A short walk to groceries and food and the J and M trains makes it easy to get into and out of the city. There is also a bus out side but I cannot say I know the route. the appt is a one bedroom with a couch (bed) in a well appointed bldg. An outside BBQ, game room, laundry room, and gym make this a good place to stay. Not much seating and a few basic dishes make it functional, but don't plan to host a dinner party. The property is very quiet and the neighbor hood is as well.
